column3: Definition
Privacy Term related to Tracking
Privacy Term that indicates Tracking is allowed
Privacy Term that indicates Tracking is allowed but only by the 1st Party
Privacy Term that indicates Tracking is not allowed
Privacy Term that indicates Tracking is not allowed by 3rd Parties
Privacy Term that indicates Tracking is allowed but only if it uses non-PII
Privacy Term that indicates Tracking is allowed but only if it does not involve Fingerprinting
Privacy Term that indicates Tracking involving use of PII is not allowed
Privacy Term that indicates Tracking involving use of Fingerprinting is not allowed
Privacy Term related to Profiling
Privacy Term that indicates Profiling is allowed
Privacy Term that indicates Profiling is allowed but only by the 1st Party
Privacy Term that indicates Profiling is not allowed
Privacy Term that indicates Profiling is not allowed by 3rd Parties
Privacy Term that indicates Profiling is allowed but only if it uses non-PII
Privacy Term that indicates Profiling is allowed but only if it does not involve Fingerprinting
Privacy Term that indicates Profiling involving use of PII is not allowed
Privacy Term that indicates Profiling involving use of Fingerprinting is not allowed
Privacy Term related to Data Sharing
Privacy Term that indicates Data Sharing is allowed only if the data is fully anonymised
Privacy Term that indicates Data Sharing is not allowed even if the data is fully anonymised
Privacy Term that indicates Data Sharing is allowed
Privacy Term that indicates Data Sharing is not allowed
Privacy Term related to interpretation of the Privacy Term(s) using deontic logic
Privacy Term that indicates a permissive interpretation where if something is not prohibited or if there are no rules governing it, then it is assumed to be permitted
Privacy Term that indicates a prohibitive interpretation where if something is not permitted or if there are no rules governing it, then it is assumed to be prohibited
Privacy Term related to resolving conflicts in Privacy Term(s)
Privacy Term that indicates a conflict should be resolved by preferring the permission over the prohibition i.e. if something is both prohibited and permitted, it is assumed to be permitted
Privacy Term that indicates a conflict should be resolved by preferring the prohibition over the permission i.e. if something is both prohibited and permitted, it is assumed to be prohibited
Privacy Term that indicates a conflict should be resolved by discarding the conflicting terms i.e. removing all terms that are in conflict

Privacy Term that indicates a conflict should be resolved using the specified method but only for this context i.e. other contexts that have their own conflict resolution method should not be overridden
Privacy Term that indicates this conflict method should be used to resolve all conflicts across contexts i.e. other contexts that have their own conflict resolution method should be overridden
Privacy Term that indicates the behaviour of the Privacy Agent
Privacy Term that indicates the behaviour of the Privacy Agent in relation to requests
Privacy Term that indicates the Privacy Agent should allow requests to be made

column2: Agent Allows Requests Only Known Party
column3: Privacy Term that indicates the Privacy Agent should allow requests to be made but only from prior known parties

column2: Agent Allows Requests Only Prior Agreement Party
column3: Privacy Term that indicates the Privacy Agent should allow requests to be made but only from prior known parties with whom an agreement was established in the past
Privacy Term that indicates the Privacy Agent should not allow any requests to be made
Privacy Term that indicates the behaviour of the Privacy Agent in relation to negotiations
Privacy Term that indicates the Privacy Agent should allow negotiations

column2: Agent Allows Negotiation Only Known Party
column3: Privacy Term that indicates the Privacy Agent should allow negotiations but only from known parties

column2: Agent Allows Negotiation Only Prior Agreement Party
column3: Privacy Term that indicates the Privacy Agent should allow negotiations but only from known parties with whom an agreement was established in the past
Privacy Term that indicates the Privacy Agent should not allow any negotiations
Privacy Term that indicates the applicability of Privacy Preference(s)
Privacy Term that indicates the privacy preference always applies in all contexts and should always be used in agreements and negotiations
Privacy Term that indicates the privacy preference never applies in any context and should never be used in agreements or negotiations
Privacy Term that indicates the privacy preference conditionally applies i.e. it should only be used in agreements and negotiations if the associated condition is satisfied within the context
Privacy Term that indicates portability of data from service provider to individual
Privacy Term that indicates data should be ported or made available immediately without delay
Privacy Term that indicates data should be ported or made available on request
Privacy Term that indicates data should be ported or made available to third party
Privacy Term that indicates data portability is not required to be provided
Privacy Term that indicates transparency as an obligation
Privacy Term that indicates transparency is obligated ahead of intended process i.e. ex-ante transparency
Privacy Term that indicates transparency is obligated after intended process i.e. ex-post transparency
Privacy Term that indicates transparency is obligated upon request
Privacy Term that indicates transparency is not required to be provided
Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding purposes involved for processing of data and technologies as an obligation

Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding purposes involved for processing of data and technologies is obligated ahead of intended process i.e. ex-ante transparency regarding purposes involved for processing of data and technologies

Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding purposes involved for processing of data and technologies is obligated after intended process i.e. ex-post transparency regarding purposes involved for processing of data and technologies
Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding purposes involved for processing of data and technologies is obligated upon request
Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding purposes involved for processing of data and technologies is not required to be provided
Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles as an obligation

Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles is obligated ahead of intended process i.e. ex-ante transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles

Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles is obligated after intended process i.e. ex-post transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles
Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles is obligated upon request
Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding identities and involvement of parties in specific roles is not required to be provided
Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding data involved and its source as an obligation
Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding data involved and its source is obligated ahead of intended process i.e. ex-ante transparency regarding data involved and its source
Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding data involved and its source is obligated after intended process i.e. ex-post transparency regarding data involved and its source
Privacy Term that indicates transparency regarding data involved and its source is obligated upon request
